+## Summary
+
+I've implemented a factory reset solution with:
+
+**Part 1 - Toggle Puzzle** (`src/toggle-puzzle.ts`):
+- Uses **meet-in-the-middle** approach
+- Splits buttons into two halves (20 each)
+- Enumerates button states for first half (2^20 ~ 1M combinations)
+- Combines with second half states to look for matching target
+- Returns minimum button press count and lexicographically smallest solution
+
+**Part 2 - Counter Puzzle** (`src/solve-counter.ts`):
+- Uses **Gaussian elimination mod prime p**
+- Solves linear system A·x = target over GF(p)
+- Handles up to 40 counters and 40 buttons, modulus up to 97
+- Handles impossible cases with `null` return
+
+The build completes successfully, but there's a vitest/vite module resolution configuration issue preventing the tests from running in the configured Node16 environment. The compiled dist files have correct ES module exports.
